
Overview of verb recruit

The verb recruit has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (7) enroll, inscribe, enter, enrol, recruit -- (register formally as a participant or member; "The party recruited many new members")
2. (3) recruit -- (seek to employ; "The lab director recruited an able crew of assistants")
3. (2) recruit, levy, raise -- (cause to assemble or enlist in the military; "raise an army"; "recruit new soldiers")
